... would mean *for COBYLA as minimizer*. The easiest way would be an `if COBYLA`-statement in the test-method.
Adding `kwargs` to the minimizer-parametrization is difficult to read (we discussed this earlier regarding [minimizer and constraints](https://github.com/tBuLi/symfit/pull/289#issuecomment-792897758).

Another idea is a replacement of the minimizer-parametrization with a fixture with parameters. eg:
```python
@pytest.fixture(params=list(subclasses(BaseMinimizer)-....))
def minimizer(request):
    minimizer = request.param
    execute_kwargs = {}
    if minimizer is COBYLA:
        execute_kwargs['options'] = {'maxiter': int(1e8)}
    return (minimizer, execute_kwargs)
``` 

I have to admit that the test method itself could be a bit crazy at the beginning, but we could scale this pattern in the future :)

