@Irving-cl Unfortunatelly the IsCslEnabled method is not returning real state of CSL. The flag "RxOnWhenIdle" is stored in two places (MLE)[https://github.com/openthread/openthread/blob/main/src/core/thread/mle.hpp#L1611] and (MAC)[https://github.com/openthread/openthread/blob/main/src/core/mac/mac.hpp#L855]. During transitions between SSED -> MED and MED -> SSED those two aren't synchronized. 
The synchronization happens in sending child update request (here)[https://github.com/openthread/openthread/blob/main/src/core/thread/mle.cpp#L2366] or on reception of child update request reply (here)[https://github.com/openthread/openthread/blob/main/src/core/thread/mle.cpp#L3840]. Ofcourse both of those places are already to late to EnableCsl.
That's why I added extra method which is independent from `IsRxOnWhenIdle` from MAC.

